pole is gonna frighten patients.

32
00:01:46,873 --> 00:01:47,966
That's a good point.

33
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:50,875
Why don't we just, uh, do this.

34
00:01:52,245 --> 00:01:53,304
There we go.

35
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:55,576
Meet Earl, my new sidekick.

36
00:01:56,083 --> 00:01:57,551
Oh, yeah, that's much better.

37
00:01:57,651 --> 00:01:59,483
Right? A smiling bag of poison.

38
00:01:59,553 --> 00:02:00,680
Yep, going full chemo.

39
00:02:00,754 --> 00:02:02,154
Please don't say that. Got it.

40
00:02:02,222 --> 00:02:06,250
I know that at some
point I'm gonna be useless.

41
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,856
Thanks for not disagreeing.

42
00:02:08,929 --> 00:02:10,659
Well, we both
know what's coming.

43
00:02:10,731 --> 00:02:14,190
And, uh, after what happened in Cold Spring,
I can't just let the hospital fall apart.

44
00:02:14,267 --> 00:02:17,931
I mean, I need to find someone
who can, you know, take over

